1.title: The Light Bulb Scene
1.plot: BoJack has misgivings about his new show. Princess Carolyn visits an adoption agency. Todd interviews for a job at WhatTimeIsItRightNow.com.

2.title: The Dog Days Are Over
2.plot: Diane divorces Mr. Peanutbutter and moves into a shabby studio. Feeling melancholy, she travels to Vietnam to get away from it all.

3.title: Planned Obsolescence
3.plot: Todd meet's Yolanda's parents, who don't know she's asexual. Mr. Peanutbutter romances a young waitress. Gina confesses a childhood dream to BoJack.

4.title: BoJack the Feminist
4.plot: When Princess Carolyn casts a disgraced celeb in "Philbert," BoJack inadvertently takes a stand. Mr. Peanutbutter tries to toughen up his image.

5.title: The Amelia Earheart Story
5.plot: Painful memories come rushing back when Princess Carolyn visits her hometown and meets a pregnant teen. A stunt goes awry on the "Philbert" set.

6.title: Free Churro
6.plot: BoJack delivers a eulogy at a funeral.

7.title: INT. SUB
7.plot: Diane's therapist encourages her to set boundaries with BoJack. A missing string cheese ignites a dispute between Todd and Princess Carolyn.

8.title: Mr. Peanutbutter's Boos
8.plot: At BoJack's 25th annual Halloween party, Pickles gets a crash course in Mr. Peanutbutter's romantic history -- and some advice from Diane.

9.title: Ancient History
9.plot: A visiting Hollyhock dumps BoJack's painkillers, sending him on a desperate search for more. Todd tries to solve Emily's dating dilemma.

10.title: Head in the Clouds
10.plot: At the "Philbert" premiere party, Princess Carolyn deftly negotiates a deal, Gina steps into the limelight, and Diane confronts BoJack.

11.title: The Showstopper
11.plot: "Philbert" is a hit, and filming begins on Season 2. But as BoJack spirals deeper into addiction, he loses his grip on reality.

12.title: The Stopped Show
12.plot: In the midst of the latest PR crisis, Princess Carolyn gets a life-changing opportunity. With Diane's help, BoJack finally faces the music.

1.title: BoJack Horseman: The BoJack Horseman Story, Chapter One
1.plot: A publishing house eagerly awaits BoJack's memoirs, but he hasn't even started yet. His agent/ex and his publisher try to talk him into working with a ghost writer, but BoJack's too despondent about being washed up to focus.

2.title: BoJack Hates the Troops
2.plot: BoJack gets into trouble after taking muffins a Navy Seal had "dibs" on and then calling American soldiers jerks on live television.

3.title: Prickly Muffin
3.plot: A child actress from the sitcom BoJack starred in 20 years ago shows up at his house leading to a series of chaotic events.

4.title: Zoës and Zeldas
4.plot: Bojack mentors Todd in his upcoming career; meanwhile Diane's ex-boyfriend writes an article about Mr. Peanutbutter for an online article.

5.title: Live Fast, Diane Nguyen
5.plot: A business trip for BoJack and Diane takes a detour; Todd runs a scam that gets him in trouble.

6.title: Our A-Story Is a 'D' Story
6.plot: In a bout of drunken jealousy toward Mr. Peanutbutter, BoJack steals the "D" from the Hollywood sign for Diane. Meanwhile, Todd finds himself juggling two very demanding dates.

7.title: Say Anything
7.plot: Princess Carolyn tries to have it all and prove she's the best agent in the biz, while Bojack, Todd, and Vanessa Gecko make it as difficult as possible.

8.title: The Telescope
8.plot: When he learns his old friend from "Horsin' Around" is dying, BoJack tries to mend fences.

9.title: Horse Majeure
9.plot: A love struck BoJack tries to sabotage a wedding; Todd accepts a surprising new professional role.

10.title: One Trick Pony
10.plot: BoJack shoots a movie at Mr. Peanutbutter's house; Diane finishes her book.

11.title: Downer Ending
11.plot: BoJack embarks on a project in his typically gonzo style, leading to a drug-fueled revelation.

12.title: Later
12.plot: Months after his memoir is released, BoJack's being considered for a role that's a life long dream.

0.title: BoJack Horseman Christmas Special: Sabrina's Christmas Wish
0.plot: BoJack and Todd watch a very special Christmas episode of "Horsin' Around" to celebrate the holidays.

1.title: Brand New Couch
1.plot: Picking up where he left off, Bojack Horseman is now set to start filming his dream movie Secretariat.

2.title: Yesterdayland
2.plot: BoJack is drawn to the one female in town who has no idea who he is (because she was in a coma). Todd opens a theme park.

3.title: Still Broken
3.plot: A funeral turns into a treasure hunt for the "Horsin' Around" cast and a potential schmoozefest for Princess Carolyn and Mr. Peanutbutter. Meanwhile, Todd briefly reinvents himself.

4.title: After the Party
4.plot: Mr. Peanutbutter throws Diane a surprise birthday party, putting tension on their relationship. Princess Carolyn and Vincent have a serious talk. Wanda tells BoJack a joke.

5.title: Chickens
5.plot: Todd tries to save a chicken from the slaughter house while Bojack and Kelsey are allowed some bonding time.

6.title: Higher Love
6.plot: Princess Carolyn sees an opportunity when Mr. Peanutbutter's agent dies. BoJack flips when he says the "L" word out loud to Wanda.

7.title: Hank After Dark
7.plot: Diane goes off script during BoJack's book tour, jeopardizing Mr. Peanutbutter's new show. Todd gets involved in international affairs.

8.title: Let's Find Out
8.plot: BoJack Horseman is a contestant on Mr. Peanutbutter's new game show, facing off against a mystery 'bigger celebrity' contestant.

9.title: The Shot
9.plot: BoJack, Kelsey, Todd, Princess Carolyn, and Mr. Peanutbutter attempt to shoot a crucial scene in the Secretariat movie that was not in the script. Princess Carolyn and Diane contemplate their respective careers.

10.title: Yes And
10.plot: Diane crashes at BoJack's place after quitting her job following Sebastian St. Clair, which puts a strain on BoJack and Wanda's relationship. Todd joins an improv comedy troupe which turns out to be a cult.

11.title: Escape from L.A.
11.plot: Bojack runs off to New Mexico to reconnect with an old friend, only to find she's happily married with a family. After staying longer than planned, Bojack makes another life mistake.

12.title: Out to Sea
12.plot: BoJack discovers the Secretariat film was finished without him. Princess Carolyn starts her own agency firm. Todd finds himself trapped in the improv comedy cult.

1.title: Start Spreading the News
1.plot: Bojack and goes to New York to be interviewed for his new film. Todd tags along and realizes he bit off a little more than he could chew.

2.title: The BoJack Horseman Show
2.plot: It's 2007, and Princess Carolyn works tirelessly to get Bojack to stop basking in the light of the glory days and start working again. Diane and Mr. Peanutbutter meet, and Todd kisses a girl.

3.title: BoJack Kills
3.plot: Bojack is framed for a murder. Meanwhile, Todd and Mr. Peanutbutter are sprayed by a skunk.

4.title: Fish Out of Water
4.plot: As Bojack is forced to attend an underwater movie festival to promote his new movie, a series of events and the inability to communicate with underwater life ensures that not everything goes as planned.

5.title: Love And/Or Marriage
5.plot: While Todd and Bojack crash a rehearsal dinner, Diane gets high with a client. Princess Carolyn goes on a series of blind dates.

6.title: Brrap Brrap Pew Pew
6.plot: Diane's tweet lands Sextina Aquafina in hot water. Prankster and A-list actor Jurj Clooners gets under BoJack's skin.

7.title: Stop the Presses
7.plot: Todd builds a giant papier-mâché Todd head. A customer service rep gives Bojack some good advice when he tries to cancel his newspaper subscription.

8.title: Old Acquaintance
8.plot: Bojack is up for a part in David Pincher's latest film. Diane meets Mr. Peanutbutter's brother and Todd takes the business in a new direction.

9.title: Best Thing That Ever Happened
9.plot: After Princess Carolyn's latest mistake as BoJack's agent gets worse and worse, their entire relationship comes into question.

10.title: It's You
10.plot: Mr. Peanutbutter announces the Oscar nominees. Bojack surrounds himself with admires, not realizing how much his true friendships are falling apart.

11.title: That's Too Much, Man!
11.plot: Bojack gets Sarah Lynn to break her sobriety to help drown his depression, and experiences the next few months through blackouts

12.title: That Went Well
12.plot: Bojack hits rock bottom. Mr. Peanutbutter and Todd save the day. Princess Carolyn finds a new calling

1.title: See Mr. Peanutbutter Run
1.plot: Mr. Peanutbutter starts his campaign for Governor of California by challenging the current governor to a ski race while BoJack is nowhere to be found.

2.title: The Old Sugarman Place
2.plot: BoJack goes off the grid and winds up at his grandparents' dilapidated home in Michigan where he reflects on his family legacy and befriends another soul haunted by the past.

3.title: Hooray! Todd Episode!
3.plot: Helpful to a fault, Todd is spread thin doing favors for Princess Carolyn, Mr. Peanutbutter and a visitor with a potential connection to BoJack.

4.title: Commence Fracking
4.plot: The campaign takes a toll on Diane's love life. BoJack helps Hollyhock search for her mom. Princess Carolyn tries to get pregnant.

5.title: Thoughts and Prayers
5.plot: A mass shooting at a mall creates a PR nightmare for Princess Carolyn. BoJack takes Hollyhock to visit his estranged mother.

6.title: Stupid Piece of Sh*t
6.plot: Surrounded by family, BoJack spirals into self-loathing. Princess Carolyn and Rutabaga Rabitowitz plan Courtney and Todd's sham wedding.

7.title: Underground
7.plot: Mr. Peanutbutter's posh campaign fundraiser takes a terrifying turn. As chaos swirls around them. BoJack and Diane get drunk.

8.title: The Judge
8.plot: Hollyhock starts dating an intern on BoJack's new show. Princess Carolyn meets Ralph's parents. Mr. Peanutbutter throws his support behind Woodchuck.

9.title: Ruthie
9.plot: On one awful day, Princess Carolyn deals with rejection, deception and loss. BoJack and Diane try to track down Hollyhock's birth certificate.

10.title: lovin that cali lifestyle!!
10.plot: Diane leaks damaging information on Jessica Biel, Todd's clown dentist business hits a snag, and Princess Carolyn finds hope in an unlikely place.

11.title: Time's Arrow
11.plot: In 1963, young socialite Beatrice Sugarman meets the rebellious Butterscotch Horseman at her debutante party.

12.title: What Time Is It Right Now
12.plot: Princess Carolyn pitches "Philbert" to company execs. Todd gets a better business idea. BoJack comes to a realization about Hollyhock.

1.plot:

imdb.title: BoJack Horseman
plot: _BoJack Horseman_ (qv) was the star of the hit TV show "Horsin' Around" in the '90s, now he's washed up, living in Hollywood, complaining about everything, and wearing colorful sweaters.::Ian Collins
